features.plan:
Plan to Harden Security and Verify Build once scaffold exists:

1) Initialize scaffold (if not already present)
- Preferred: generate in-place at repo root
  - Option A: pnpm create electron-vite@latest .  (choose React + TypeScript)
  - If in-place generation is not allowed due to non-empty dir: pnpm create electron-vite@latest temp-app (React + TS), then move files from temp-app/* to repo root and delete temp-app.
- Ensure scripts in package.json:
  - dev: electron-vite dev
  - build: electron-vite build && electron-builder
  - lint: eslint . --ext .ts,.tsx,.js,.cjs --max-warnings 0
  - format: prettier --write .
- Ensure TypeScript configs exist in root and per package (electron/main, electron/preload, electron/renderer).
- Ensure ESLint and Prettier configs exist (.eslintrc.*, .prettierrc or prettier.config.cjs).

2) Security hardening in electron/main/index.ts
- Create BrowserWindow with secure webPreferences:
  webPreferences: {
    preload: path.join(__dirname, '../preload/index.js'),
    contextIsolation: true,
    sandbox: true,
    nodeIntegration: false,
    webSecurity: true,
    devTools: process.env.NODE_ENV !== 'production'
  }
- Disallow untrusted navigation and window opens:
  mainWindow.webContents.setWindowOpenHandler(({ url }) => {
    // Optionally allow only https: via shell.openExternal and deny creating new windows
    return { action: 'deny' };
  });
  mainWindow.webContents.on('will-navigate', (e, url) => {
    // Allow only same-origin during dev (VITE_DEV_SERVER_URL) or file:// in prod
    const isDev = !!process.env.VITE_DEV_SERVER_URL;
    const allowed = isDev ? url.startsWith(process.env.VITE_DEV_SERVER_URL || '') : url.startsWith('file://');
    if (!allowed) e.preventDefault();
  });
- Avoid enableRemoteModule; keep default false.
- Optionally set app.commandLine.appendSwitch('disable-features', 'OutOfBlinkCors'); NOT recommended; keep defaults secure.

3) Preload isolation and API exposure (electron/preload/index.ts)
- Use contextBridge to expose a minimal, typed API only:
  import { contextBridge, ipcRenderer } from 'electron';
  contextBridge.exposeInMainWorld('api', {
    ping: () => ipcRenderer.invoke('ping')
  });
- In main process: ipcMain.handle('ping', () => 'pong');

4) Renderer CSP and safety
- In electron/renderer/index.html add a CSP meta for production builds:
  <meta http-equiv="Content-Security-Policy" content="default-src 'self'; script-src 'self'; style-src 'self' 'unsafe-inline'; img-src 'self' data:; connect-src 'self'; font-src 'self'; frame-ancestors 'none'; base-uri 'self';" />
  Note: During dev, Vite HMR requires ws: and dev server origin; configure conditionally or accept more permissive CSP only in dev.

5) Verify dev and build
- pnpm install
- pnpm run dev -> confirm Electron launches with React placeholder UI.
- pnpm run build -> confirm dist contains a runnable app (e.g., dist/mac|win-unpacked|linux-unpacked). Launch the built binary to validate it runs.

6) Lint/format
- pnpm run lint -> zero errors/warnings or address any.
- pnpm run format -> ensure Prettier applies formatting.

7) Optional build security
- In electron-builder config (package.json or electron-builder.yml), enable asar: true and set files filters to exclude dev-only artifacts.
